aura.name: aura
aura.description: Aura is an app designed to help blind individuals independently match their outfits using machine learning and RFID technology. It works by scanning clothing tags embedded with RFID chips to identify colors, patterns, and textures. The app then provides guidance on matching clothes based on color theory. Aura has won several awards, including GEMASTIK XVII and Microsoft's AI for Accessibility.

mimicri.name: mimicri
mimicri.description: Mimicri helps painters achieve target colors by providing accurate color mixing formulas using UIKit, VIPER architecture, SwiftData, Combine, and the Kubelka-Munk theory, with CI/CD implementation.

weather-way.name: weather-way
weather-way.description: WeatherWay is a weather app built using SwiftUI, WeatherKit, and MapKit, designed to provide weather alerts for your route.

intone.name: intone
intone.description: Intone is a private voice-sharing app that lets people send secure voice notes to loved ones; added Face ID for privacy and built the experience with SwiftUI, AVFoundation, Lottie, WidgetKit, and Supabase.
